&lt;p&gt;Thanks for the contribution!&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13869790" author="lehmi" created="Mon, 13 Jan 2014 18:19:17 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Just for the record, my linux environment doesn&apos;t know anything about the class CLibJpegImageWriter. I got one writer only for jpegs JPEGImageWriter.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13869812" author="abrin" created="Mon, 13 Jan 2014 18:38:07 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=lehmi&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;lehmi&quot;&gt;lehmi&lt;/a&gt; I agree, removing one specific writer was a less than ideal idea; but it was an attempt to try and isolate the writer &amp;#8211; it, BTW, failed.  The NULL-check does seem to address the issue.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
